"Students" means students from a broad range of backgrounds and circumstances, including:
Disadvantaged students;
Students with diverse racial, ethnic, and cultural backgrounds;
Students with disabilities;
Students with limited English proficiency;
Students who have dropped out of school; and
Academically talented students.

"Technology" means the latest state-of-the-art technology products and services, including:
Closed circuit television systems;
Educational television and radio broadcasting;
Cable television;
Satellite;
Copper and fiber-optic transmission;
Computer and computer-based technology;
Video and audio laser and CD ROM discs;
Video and audio tapes or other technologies; and
Web-based resources and courses.
